      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The key test: if the value were committed to a public repository, would it enable an attacker to do harm? If yes, it is a secret. If no, it is config."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Storing Non-Secret Config"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Non-secret config belongs in version control alongside the application code. Use separate files per environment so differences are explicit and reviewable:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# k8s/prod/configmap.yaml  (committed to repo)\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: claude-app-config\n  namespace: prod\ndata:\n  APP_ENV: \"prod\"\n  LOG_LEVEL: \"WARNING\"\n  MAX_TOKENS: \"1024\"\n  REPLICA_MIN: \"3\"\n  REPLICA_MAX: \"20\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# k8s/staging/configmap.yaml  (committed to repo)\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: claude-app-config\n  namespace: staging\ndata:\n  APP_ENV: \"staging\"\n  LOG_LEVEL: \"INFO\"\n  MAX_TOKENS: \"1024\"\n  REPLICA_MIN: \"2\"\n  REPLICA_MAX: \"2\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Because these files are in version control, any change to them creates a PR, goes through code review, and is tracked in git history \u2014 giving you a full audit trail of every config change."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Storing Secrets"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kubernetes Secrets"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The simplest approach for a Kubernetes deployment is a Kubernetes Secret. The secret is stored in etcd (encrypted at rest if the cluster is configured correctly) and mounted as environment variables by the pod spec."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Create the secret imperatively (never store the value in a file)\nkubectl create secret generic claude-api-credentials   --from-literal=ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"sk-ant-...\"   --namespace prod\n\n# Reference in the deployment \u2014 the value is injected at runtime\n# Never echo the key value in CI logs\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# k8s/prod/deployment.yaml \u2014 reference, not value\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: app\n      envFrom:\n        - configMapRef:\n            name: claude-app-config     # non-secret config\n      env:\n        - name: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: claude-api-credentials\n              key: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n        - name: DATABASE_URL\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: claude-db-credentials\n              key: DATABASE_URL\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "AWS SSM Parameter Store"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For teams using AWS, SSM Parameter Store with SecureString type provides rotation, versioning, and IAM-based access control without a separate secrets manager deployment:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/secrets.py \u2014 load secrets from SSM at startup\nimport boto3, os, functools\n\n_ssm = boto3.client(\"ssm\", region_name=os.environ.get(\"AWS_REGION\", \"us-east-1\"))\n\n@functools.lru_cache(maxsize=None)\ndef get_secret(name: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Fetch a SecureString from SSM Parameter Store (cached per process).\"\"\"\n    response = _ssm.get_parameter(Name=name, WithDecryption=True)\n    return response[\"Parameter\"][\"Value\"]\n\ndef load_all_secrets():\n    \"\"\"Load all application secrets from SSM at startup.\"\"\"\n    env = os.environ.get(\"APP_ENV\", \"dev\")\n    os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"] = get_secret(f\"/claude-app/{env}/anthropic-api-key\")\n    os.environ[\"DATABASE_URL\"]      = get_secret(f\"/claude-app/{env}/database-url\")\n    os.environ[\"SIGNING_KEY\"]       = get_secret(f\"/claude-app/{env}/signing-key\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fail-Fast Config Validation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Load and validate all configuration at startup, before the application accepts any traffic. This converts missing or malformed configuration from a runtime error (caught when a user hits a broken endpoint) into a startup failure (caught immediately in CI or at deploy time):"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/config.py \u2014 load and validate all config at startup\nimport os, sys\n\n# Non-secret config: baked in (MODEL_VERSION) or from ConfigMap (others)\nMODEL_VERSION = os.environ.get(\"MODEL_VERSION\", \"\")\nAPP_ENV = os.environ.get(\"APP_ENV\", \"\")\nLOG_LEVEL = os.environ.get(\"LOG_LEVEL\", \"INFO\")\nMAX_TOKENS = int(os.environ.get(\"MAX_TOKENS\", \"1024\"))\n\n# Secrets: injected from Kubernetes Secret or SSM\nANTHROPIC_API_KEY = os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\", \"\")\n\nVALID_ENVS = {\"dev\", \"sandbox\", \"staging\", \"prod\"}\nVALID_LOG_LEVELS = {\"DEBUG\", \"INFO\", \"WARNING\", \"ERROR\"}\n\ndef validate():\n    errors = []\n\n    if not MODEL_VERSION:\n        errors.append(\"MODEL_VERSION is not set (should be baked into image)\")\n    if APP_ENV not in VALID_ENVS:\n        errors.append(f\"APP_ENV={APP_ENV!r} is not one of {VALID_ENVS}\")\n    if LOG_LEVEL not in VALID_LOG_LEVELS:\n        errors.append(f\"LOG_LEVEL={LOG_LEVEL!r} is not valid\")\n    if MAX_TOKENS < 1 or MAX_TOKENS > 8192:\n        errors.append(f\"MAX_TOKENS={MAX_TOKENS} is out of range [1, 8192]\")\n    if not ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:\n        errors.append(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is not set\")\n    if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY and not ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.startswith(\"sk-ant-\"):\n        errors.append(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY does not look like a valid Anthropic key\")\n\n    if errors:\n        for e in errors:\n            print(f\"CONFIG ERROR: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    return True\n\n# Call at module import so it runs before anything else\nvalidate()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secret Rotation Without Redeployment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kubernetes Secrets can be updated in-place without restarting pods \u2014 but the pod must re-read the secret. Two patterns:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern 1: Reload on schedule"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/api_client.py \u2014 refresh secret on a schedule\nimport threading, time, os\n\n_lock = threading.Lock()\n_client = None\n_last_refresh = 0\n_REFRESH_INTERVAL = 3600  # 1 hour\n\ndef get_client():\n    global _client, _last_refresh\n    now = time.monotonic()\n    if _client is None or now - _last_refresh > _REFRESH_INTERVAL:\n        with _lock:\n            if _client is None or now - _last_refresh > _REFRESH_INTERVAL:\n                from anthropic import Anthropic\n                # Re-read from env (Kubernetes mounts update automatically)\n                _client = Anthropic(api_key=os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"])\n                _last_refresh = now\n    return _client\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern 2: Rolling restart after rotation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# After updating the Kubernetes Secret, trigger a rolling restart\n# so pods reload the new key from the updated secret\nkubectl rollout restart deployment/claude-app -n prod\nkubectl rollout status deployment/claude-app -n prod --timeout=120s\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detecting Accidental Secret Leakage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The most common leakage vectors are log statements that print environment variables and error messages that include request context containing API keys. Prevent both:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/logging_config.py \u2014 redact secrets from logs\nimport logging, os, re\n\n# Build a set of secret values to redact\n_SECRETS = {v for k, v in os.environ.items()\n            if any(word in k for word in (\"KEY\", \"SECRET\", \"TOKEN\", \"PASSWORD\", \"URL\"))\n            if v}  # non-empty only\n\nclass SecretRedactor(logging.Filter):\n    \"\"\"Remove known secret values from log records before emission.\"\"\"\n    def filter(self, record):\n        msg = str(record.getMessage())\n        for secret in _SECRETS:\n            if secret in msg and len(secret) > 8:   # avoid redacting short, common values\n                msg = msg.replace(secret, \"[REDACTED]\")\n        record.msg = msg\n        record.args = ()\n        return True\n\ndef configure_logging():\n    logger = logging.getLogger()\n    logger.addFilter(SecretRedactor())\n    logging.basicConfig(\n        level=os.environ.get(\"LOG_LEVEL\", \"INFO\"),\n        format=\"%(asctime)s %(levelname)s %(name)s %(message)s\",\n    )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Also add a CI step that scans for hardcoded secrets in every PR:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/ci.yml \u2014 secret scanning\n  secret-scan:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0   # full history for scanning\n\n      - name: Scan for hardcoded secrets\n        uses: trufflesecurity/trufflehog@main\n        with:\n          path: ./\n          base: ${{ github.event.repository.default_branch }}\n          head: HEAD\n          extra_args: --only-verified\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Access Control for Secrets"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kubernetes RBAC and cloud IAM both provide fine-grained control over which workloads and which people can read each secret:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# k8s/prod/rbac.yaml \u2014 only the app service account can read prod secrets\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: claude-app-secret-reader\n  namespace: prod\nrules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    resourceNames: [\"claude-api-credentials\", \"claude-db-credentials\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\"]\n\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: claude-app-secret-reader-binding\n  namespace: prod\nsubjects:\n  - kind: ServiceAccount\n    name: claude-app\n    namespace: prod\nroleRef:\n  kind: Role\n  name: claude-app-secret-reader\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "With this RBAC configuration, only pods running under the 'claude-app' ServiceAccount in the 'prod' namespace can read the production secrets. Engineers cannot kubectl get secret to read the key value unless they have been explicitly granted additional access."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Verify access control: this should return Forbidden for a regular developer\nkubectl auth can-i get secret/claude-api-credentials -n prod --as=developer@company.com\n\n# Only the service account should succeed\nkubectl auth can-i get secret/claude-api-credentials -n prod   --as=system:serviceaccount:prod:claude-app\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Non-secret config (APP_ENV, LOG_LEVEL, MAX_TOKENS) belongs in version control in per-environment ConfigMap files; any change creates a reviewable PR"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Secrets (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, DATABASE_URL) must never appear in version control \u2014 store them in Kubernetes Secrets, HashiCorp Vault, or AWS SSM Parameter Store"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reference secrets in the pod spec using secretKeyRef, not by value; the Kubernetes control plane injects them as environment variables at runtime"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Validate all configuration at application startup with explicit assertions; missing or malformed config should cause a startup failure, not a runtime error"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use either scheduled re-reads or rolling restarts to rotate API keys without downtime"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add a log-level SecretRedactor filter that replaces known secret values with [REDACTED] before log emission"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Include TruffleHog or a similar secret scanner in CI to catch any accidental hardcoded secrets before they reach the main branch"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}